.TH $file-template 5
.XI $file-template - "Regular expression file search string" 
.SH NAME
$file-template \- Regular expression file search string
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB$file-template\fR "\fIstring\fR"; Default is ""
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B $file-template
defines a regular expression search string used to identify a file in the
.Ht grep 3
and 
.Ht compile 3
buffers. The format of the string is the same as magic mode search
strings (see 
.Ht search-forward 2 ).
.SH EXAMPLE
A  \s-1UNIX\s0  file name may be  considered  to contain  any ASCII  character
except a space or a  '\fC:\fR'  (used as a  divider  in many  programs).  Thus
\fB$file-template\fR should be:
.Me $emf-scheme
.CS
set-variable $file-template "[!-9;-z]+"
.CE
.Me $ehf-scheme
This will correctly identify "\fCfoo.c\fR" in the following example.
.CS
foo.c: 45:      printf("hello world\\n") ;
.CE 0
